            1975</docTitle><sourceNote>(Format changes—<ref href="hk/2020/er3">E.R. 3 of
            2020</ref>)<marker role="blank-line"></marker><marker role="blank-line"></marker></sourceNote><content class="align_justified first_line_indent_18"><inline class="small_caps">By His
                Excellency Sir CRAWFORD MURRAY MacLEHOSE</inline>, Knight Commander of the Most
            Distinguished Order of Saint Michael and Saint George, Knight Commander of the Royal
            Victorian Order, Member of the Most Excellent Order of the British Empire, Governor and
            Commander-in-Chief of the Colony of Hong Kong and its Dependencies.
            <marker role="blank-line"></marker></content><content class="align_justified first_line_indent_18">In exercise of the powers conferred on
            me by <ref>section 5(1)(e)</ref> of the Inland Revenue Ordinance, <ref href="/hk/cap112">Chapter 112</ref>, I hereby PROCLAIM that, in respect of the year of assessment
            commencing on the 1st April 1976, and subsequent years of assessment, property tax shall
            be charged in respect of any land or buildings or land and buildings in Areas F1, G1,
            G2, G3, G4, H1, H2, J1, K1, L1, L2, L3, M1, M2 and M3 of the New Territories, as defined
            in the <ref>Schdule</ref> to the Rating (Areas of Hong Kong) Order*.
            <marker role="blank-line"></marker></content><content class="align_justified first_line_indent_18">G<inline class="small_caps">iven</inline> under my hand and the Public Seal of the Colony of Hong Kong this
            14th day of July 1975.<marker role="blank-line"></marker><marker role="blank-line"></marker></content><content><table xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" width="400">
